Document: Shape3D
Path: godot/classes/class_shape3d.rst
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring 3D shape collision behavior, including solver bias and margin settings.

Property: custom_solver_bias (float) = 0.0
Method: set_custom_solver_bias(value: float)
Method: get_custom_solver_bias() → float
Defines how much bodies react to enforce contact separation when this shape is involved. When set to 0, uses the default contact bias from ProjectSettings.physics/3d/solver/default_contact_bias. Note: Only effective with GodotPhysics3D, has no effect with Jolt Physics.

Property: margin (float) = 0.04
Method: set_margin(value: float)
Method: get_margin() → float
Collision margin for the shape (not used in Godot Physics). Collision margins improve efficiency by adding a shell around shapes. Higher values increase performance but reduce edge accuracy.
---CHUNK---
Document: Shape3D
Path: godot/classes/class_shape3d.rst
Summary: Returns the ArrayMesh used for visualizing the collision shape in debug mode.

Method: get_debug_mesh() → ArrayMesh
Returns the ArrayMesh used to draw the debug collision for this Shape3D.